    "description": "Variance-stabilized signals for sequencing-based genomic signals.\nVariance-stabilized signals (VSS) is a signal transformation approach used for eliminating the dependency of data variance from its mean. We generate VSS for sequencing-based genomic signals by learning the empirical relationship between the mean and variance of a given signal data set and producing transformed signals that normalize for this dependence.",
